<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870220-0086 </DOCNO><HL> Owens-Corning Enters Pact</HL><DD> 02/20/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> OCFTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> TOLEDO, Ohio  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Owens-Corning Fiberglas Corp. said it reached an agreement in principle to sell its three foam-products plants to Atlas Roofing Corp., Meridian, Miss., subject to certain approvals.    Terms weren't disclosed. The maker of glass-fiber insulation and construction products said the sale is part of a restructuring plan. The plan was formulated to stave off last year's unsuccessful $2.1 billion, or $74 a share, hostile tender offer from Wickes Cos. </TEXT></DOC>